sentence: The war cry for justice was all over - Much to the chagrin of the authorities.
Slovenian: Vojni krik za pravosodje je bil vse več kot Chagrin organov.
backtrans: The war scream for justice was becoming more than Chagrin organs.

sentence: The regime's decision adumbrates the underlying agenda.
Slovenian: Odločba režima je oslabljena osnovna agenda.
backtrans: The decision of the regime is an impaired basic agenda.

sentence: The community was anxious over the passing of the much needed reforms.
Slovenian: Skupnost je bila zaskrbljena zaradi prehoda zelo potrebnih reform.
backtrans: The Community was concerned about the transition of highly needed reforms.

sentence: The think tank  published a paper outlining their apology of capital punishment.
Slovenian: Think Tank je objavil dokument, ki opisuje svojo opravičilo smrtne kazni.
backtrans: Think Tank has published a document that describes his apology of the death penalty.

sentence: Aught was left of the petition's validity
backtrans: Aight remained the validity of petition

sentence: The President exhorted his ministers to buckle up as key opposition support for his economic plan was about to buckle.
Slovenian: Predsednik je spodbudil njegove ministre, da se spomnite kot ključna opozicijska podpora za njegov gospodarski načrt, ki se je prišla na zaponko.
backtrans: The President encouraged his ministers to remember as key opposition support for his economic plan that came to the buckle.

sentence: The voters were chuffed to see the bill passed.
Slovenian: Volivci so bili ovrnjeni, da bi videli, da je bil račun opravljen.
backtrans: The voters were scrapped to see that the account was done.

sentence: The lawyer's discursive narration swayed the jury.
Slovenian: Diskurzivna pripoved odvetnika je zibala žirijo.
backtrans: The discursive narration of the lawyer rocked the jury.

sentence: The EU block opposed an eventual imposition of anti-dumping measures.
Slovenian: EU je nasprotovala morebitnemu uvedbi protidampinških ukrepov.
backtrans: The EU opposed the possible imposition of anti-dumping measures.

sentence: A fulsome eulogy was delivered by the sly counsel.
Slovenian: Fulsome Eulologiy je bil dostavljen sly nasvet.
backtrans: FulSome Eulologiy was delivered by SLY advice.

sentence: The gig-economy agency decided to garnish the refunds!
Slovenian: Agencija za gospodarstvo GIG se je odločila, da okrasijo nadomestila!
backtrans: The Gig economy agency decided to decorate the refund!

sentence: Members of the anti-theocratic revolutionary movement overthrew the peers in power!
Slovenian: Člani anti-teokratskega revolucionarnega gibanja so znižali vrstnike na oblasti!
backtrans: Members of the Anti-Theocratic Revolutionary Movement reduced peers in power!

sentence: The traitors disappointingly decided to fight with the colonialists.
Slovenian: Traitorje so se razočarale, da se bodo borili z kolonialisti.
backtrans: Treators disappointed that they will fight colonialists.
